==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|born on the 4th of July}}

===Etymology===
Refers to the {{w|Fourth of July}}, which is {{l|en|Independence Day}} in the {{l|en|United States}}. The specific phrase likely originates with the song “{{w|The Yankee Doodle Boy|Yankee Doodle Dandy}}” which opens with ''I'm a Yankee Doodle Dandy / A Yankee Doodle, do or die / A real live nephew of my {{l|en|Uncle Sam}}'s / Born on the Fourth of July''.

